On the smooth Floods , the swelling Billows rise , As if the liquid Mountains touched the Skies : Then quick they plunged , with an Impetuous hast , And seemed to speak Destruction as they passed , Yet Armed with Avarice and Curiosities

Where unmolested Streams with gentle force , Press , to their Primeveal source ; And sometime upward , gush through poreous Earth , Give to the healing Baths , a useful Birth ; ) In its more wealthy parts , the Minerals lay , And ponderous Metals , shining Nerves display : In her bright Bowels , radiant Gems
their Stupidity , no more upbraid , Who worshipped Gods , which their own Hands had made , Since we're by Gold to greater Crimes betrayed
